rs llc institutional equity investment process hudson canyon�s institutional equity investment style is large capitalization core the most important decision in the investment process is asset allocation we adhere to a policy of staying fully invested with minimal cash  we then follow a three step �topdown bottomup� investment process the three steps are sector weightings individual stock selection and portfolio construction sector weightingswe overweight underweight or equal weight our portfolios relative to the ten sectors that comprise the sp  index some of the factors we analyze in determining sector weightings include the rate of and trend in consumer spending interest rates energy prices business spending commodity prices industrial production and the strength or weakness of the us dollar individual stock selectionhudson canyon invests in the stocks of largecapitalization usbased companies and american depository receipts adrs that have long histories of success and are generally considered leaders in their industry we generally look to buy companies that are trading at the lowend of their historical valuation range we also typically seek companies that have a year earnings per share growth rate that exceeds the forward price earnings ratio and that have returns on equity of at least  we sell a stock when its current stock price becomes expensive relative to historical valuation when fundamentals deteriorate due to increasing competitive pressures or when there is an unexpected change in senior management portfolio constructionour clients� portfolios typically hold about  stocks annual turnover is generally in the  to  range the weightings of our holdings range from between  to  of the portfolio     � hudson canyon investment counselors llc  all rights reserved   active interest rate management active interest rate management the investment objective of our active interest rate management strategy attempts to maximize total return through us treasury note us bond or us treasury backed etfs appreciation secondarily our approaches seek income generation from us treasury note us bond holdings and or us treasury related etfs we believe that by improving the potential for wealth accumulation our strategies help address the risk of outliving one’s wealth without taking on equity market volatility our decision to utilize us treasuries is strategic and best accommodates our approach to interest rate risk management strategically the barclays us treasury index has over time produced returns competitive with those of the barclays government credit and barclays aggregate indices since their respective inceptions since issues of “callability” and prepayment are not an issue for treasury securities or treasury related etfs we can simplify the process to achieve our duration targets—the price sensitivity of our portfolios to changes in interest rates over time our duration strategy attempts to add value to the treasury benchmark our duration decisions are driven by our proprietary discipline—the interest rate scorecard the scorecard combines measures of economic growth inflationary expectations and investor sentiment to identify where we are in the interest rate cycle once the outlook for rates is determined in our monthly review the portfolio’s duration is setthere is no overriding of the scorecard’s output the scorecard has evolved from research begun in the s its first application to asset management was in the s and it was introduced as a “wrap platform” investment discipline at a major brokerdealer in the s we offer two related approaches in the active interest rate management strategy long only discipline and long short discipline the long only discipline has a typical duration range from  short maturity treasury bill to duration double that of the barclays us treasury index or roughly  years over time the approach will have an average duration and as a consequence yield roughly equal to that of the index or about  years the long short discipline has a typical duration range from  twice that of the index or roughly  to  years it thus has the potential to add value beyond preservation of capital long only in a rising rate environment it is best thought of as an alternative investment which complements existing bond holdings          � hudson canyon investment counselors llc  all rights reserved   hudson canyon investment counselors llc disclosure the information on this site is intended for us residents only and is not intended for distribution in any jurisdiction where hudson canyon investment counselors �hudson canyon� is not licensed to distribute such information or where the distribution of such information would be unlawful under the securities laws of such jurisdiction  hudson canyon is registered as an investment advisor with the securities and exchange commission and files notice as a federally covered advisor with florida new jersey and new york  the existence of this website should not be construed in any direct or indirect manner as a solicitation for advisory business or securities business in any state in which hudson canyon is not authorized to conduct business  further the information provided on the website is for information purposes only and should not be construed as investment advice or a determination that a particular product or service is suitable for any individual  this information should not be relied upon in making an investment decision the presentation on the web site does not purport to be a complete description of hudson canyon�s investment services all contents of this web site are protected by copyright the materials on the website may not be modified distributed posted or transmitted without the prior written consent of hudson canyon visitors to the website may print out portions of the website of interest to them for their own private use only copyright notices and other identifying information should not be removed from such printouts  website contents m